---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'worldnomads', text: 'World Nomads', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'short-term-details', text: 'Short-Term Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { href: '/insurance-for/digital-nomads', text: 'Digital Nomad Insurance' },
  { href: '/best/travel-insurance', text: 'Best Travel Insurance' },
  { href: '/providers/safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing Review' },
  { href: '/providers/img-global', text: 'IMG Global Review' },
  { href: '/providers/world-nomads', text: 'World Nomads Review' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'worldnomads', header: 'World Nomads' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Min Duration', safetywing: '4 days', img: '5 days', worldnomads: '1 day' },
  { feature: 'Max Duration', safetywing: 'Unlimited', img: '364 days', worldnomads: '365 days' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', safetywing: '$250,000', img: '$1M-5M', worldnomads: '$100K-250K' },
  { feature: 'Trip Cancellation', safetywing: 'Not included', img: 'Optional', worldnomads: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Adventure Activities', safetywing: 'Basic included', img: 'Optional rider', worldnomads: 'Excellent' },
  { feature: 'Gear/Electronics', safetywing: 'Limited', img: 'Limited', worldnomads: 'Up to $3,000' },
  { feature: 'Buy After Departure', safetywing: 'Yes', img: 'Yes', worldnomads: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Monthly Pricing', safetywing: '$45/mo', img: '$80-150/mo', worldnomads: '$100-200/mo' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'duration', header: 'Duration' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'worldnomads', header: 'World Nomads' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { duration: '1 month', safetywing: '$45', img: '$80-120', worldnomads: '$100-150' },
  { duration: '3 months', safetywing: '$135', img: '$240-360', worldnomads: '$280-400' },
  { duration: '6 months', safetywing: '$270', img: '$480-720', worldnomads: '$500-750' },
  { duration: '12 months', safetywing: '$540', img: '$960-1,400', worldnomads: '$900-1,400' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs IMG vs World Nomads for Short-Term Travel | 2025 Comparison"
  description="Compare SafetyWing, IMG Global, and World Nomads for short-term travel insurance. Expert analysis for trips lasting 1 week to 12 months."
  headline="SafetyWing vs IMG vs World Nomads: Best Short-Term Coverage"
  subheadline="Complete comparison for travelers needing flexible coverage from a few weeks to a year—comparing price, limits, and flexibility."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <section id="quick-verdict" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Quick Verdict</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">SafetyWing</h3>
        <p class="text-primary-700 mb-3">Best Budget Option</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Lowest cost at $45/month with month-to-month flexibility. Perfect for digital nomads and budget travelers who need basic medical coverage.</p>
        <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-primary-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">IMG Global</h3>
        <p class="text-purple-700 mb-3">Best Medical Coverage</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Highest limits up to $5M with comprehensive medical benefits. Best choice when serious medical protection is the priority.</p>
        <a href="/providers/img-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-purple-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">World Nomads</h3>
        <p class="text-green-700 mb-3">Best for Adventure</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Excellent adventure sports coverage and gear protection. Ideal for active travelers doing hiking, diving, or extreme sports.</p>
        <a href="/providers/world-nomads" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-green-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="comparison-table" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </section>

  <section id="safetywing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">SafetyWing</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">$45/Month</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Unlimited Duration</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Instant Purchase</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">SafetyWing's Nomad Insurance is the go-to choice for budget-conscious travelers. At $45/month (under age 40), it's significantly cheaper than alternatives while providing essential medical coverage up to $250,000. The month-to-month structure means you can cancel anytime—no annual commitment required.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Coverage can run indefinitely, making it perfect for open-ended travel. You can buy it after you've already left home, and it includes limited home country coverage (30 days per 90-day period). The main trade-off is lower limits and no trip cancellation or extensive gear coverage.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Lowest price in market</li>
          <li>• Month-to-month flexibility</li>
          <li>• Buy after departure</li>
          <li>• Unlimited duration possible</li>
          <li>• Simple online signup</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Limitations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• $250K limit (lower than others)</li>
          <li>• No trip cancellation</li>
          <li>• Limited gear coverage</li>
          <li>• Basic adventure sports only</li>
          <li>• Limited US coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="img" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">IMG Global</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Up to $5M</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Serious Medical</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">US Coverage</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">IMG Global's PatriOt Travel Medical Insurance offers the highest coverage limits for short-term travelers—up to $5 million in medical benefits. This is the choice when you're genuinely concerned about major medical events and want comprehensive protection, not just basic emergency coverage.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">IMG also stands out for US coverage options. If you're traveling to or from the United States, their plans can include full US medical benefits—crucial given American healthcare costs. The trade-off is higher premiums and a maximum duration of 364 days.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Highest limits ($1M-5M)</li>
          <li>• US coverage available</li>
          <li>• Comprehensive medical benefits</li>
          <li>• Optional adventure sports</li>
          <li>• Trip cancellation available</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Higher premiums</li>
          <li>• Max 364 days duration</li>
          <li>• Adventure sports costs extra</li>
          <li>• Less flexible than SafetyWing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/img-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-purple-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="worldnomads" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">World Nomads</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Adventure Sports</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Gear Coverage</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Trip Protection</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">World Nomads is designed for active travelers. Their adventure sports coverage is the most comprehensive in the market—over 200 activities are covered on their Explorer plan, from scuba diving to bungee jumping to motorcycle riding. If you're planning an adventure trip, World Nomads is purpose-built.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Gear and electronics coverage up to $3,000 protects your camera, laptop, and equipment—important for content creators and photographers. Trip cancellation is included, not an add-on. The trade-off is moderate medical limits ($100K-250K) and higher prices than SafetyWing.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Best adventure sports coverage</li>
          <li>• Gear/electronics up to $3K</li>
          <li>• Trip cancellation included</li>
          <li>• Buy after departure</li>
          <li>• 200+ activities covered</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Lower medical limits ($100K-250K)</li>
          <li>• Higher premiums than SafetyWing</li>
          <li>• Max 365 days coverage</li>
          <li>• US coverage limited</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/world-nomads" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-green-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get World Nomads Quote</a>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Short-Term Coverage"
    description="Get quotes for your trip duration from all three providers."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
  />

  <section id="pricing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Pricing Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">Costs vary significantly—choose based on your priorities:</p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-4">*Prices for travelers under 40, excluding US coverage. IMG and World Nomads vary by destination and coverage level. SafetyWing has consistent global pricing.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="short-term-details" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Short-Term Coverage Details</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Typical Trip Types</h3>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• Extended vacation (2-8 weeks)</li>
          <li>• Sabbatical or career break</li>
          <li>• Digital nomad trial period</li>
          <li>• Gap year or RTW travel</li>
          <li>• Remote work testing abroad</li>
          <li>• Seasonal relocation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">When to Upgrade</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Consider annual expat insurance if:</p>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• Staying in one country 6+ months</li>
          <li>• Need higher medical limits</li>
          <li>• Want routine care coverage</li>
          <li>• Have pre-existing conditions</li>
          <li>• Planning to establish residency</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Key Differences: Travel vs Expat Insurance</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Short-Term Travel Insurance</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Emergency medical focus</li>
            <li>• Trip cancellation/interruption</li>
            <li>• Gear and baggage protection</li>
            <li>• Flexible duration</li>
            <li>• Lower premiums</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Annual Expat Insurance</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Comprehensive medical</li>
            <li>• Routine and preventive care</li>
            <li>• Higher limits (often unlimited)</li>
            <li>• Pre-existing condition options</li>
            <li>• Year-long commitment</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="best-for" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Which Is Best For You?</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">Choose SafetyWing if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-primary-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• Budget is your top priority</li>
          <li>• You want month-to-month flexibility</li>
          <li>• Open-ended travel without fixed return</li>
          <li>• Basic medical coverage is sufficient</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-l-4 border-purple-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">Choose IMG Global if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-purple-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• Medical coverage is the priority</li>
          <li>• You need US coverage</li>
          <li>• Higher limits matter ($1M-5M)</li>
          <li>• You want trip cancellation options</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Choose World Nomads if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-green-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• You're doing adventure activities</li>
          <li>• Gear protection matters (cameras, laptops)</li>
          <li>• Trip cancellation coverage is important</li>
          <li>• You're an active or extreme traveler</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faqs" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Can I buy coverage after I've already left?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Yes, all three allow purchase after departure. SafetyWing is instant; IMG and World Nomads may have short waiting periods (24-72 hours) for coverage to begin after late purchase. It's always better to buy before leaving when possible.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">What happens if I extend my trip?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">SafetyWing auto-renews monthly, so you're always covered. IMG and World Nomads allow extensions up to their maximum durations (364/365 days). If you're exceeding a year abroad, consider switching to annual expat insurance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Do these cover pre-existing conditions?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Generally no—short-term travel insurance excludes pre-existing conditions. Acute onset coverage may apply (sudden emergencies from chronic conditions), but ongoing treatment isn't covered. For pre-existing conditions, you need annual expat insurance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">How do claims work?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">For emergencies, call the 24/7 assistance line first. For smaller claims, pay upfront and submit receipts via app or portal. SafetyWing has a straightforward app-based process. IMG and World Nomads may require more documentation. Reimbursement typically takes 1-4 weeks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Insurance pricing, coverage limits, and terms change frequently. Adventure sports coverage varies by specific activity and plan level. Always verify current coverage directly with providers before purchasing. This comparison is for informational purposes only and does not constitute insurance advice.</p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
